#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:61
msgid ""
"The :ref:`layer_styling_panel` provides you with some of the common "
"features of the Layer properties dialog and is a good modeless widget "
"that you can use to speed up the configuration of the layer styles and "
"view your changes on the map canvas."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:68
msgid ""
"Because properties (symbology, label, actions, default values, forms...) "
"of embedded layers (see :ref:`nesting_projects`) are pulled from the "
"original project file, and to avoid changes that may break this behavior,"
" the layer properties dialog is made unavailable for these layers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:77
msgid "Information Properties"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:79
msgid ""
"The |metadata| :guilabel:`Information` tab is read-only and represents an"
" interesting place to quickly grab summarized information and metadata "
"for the current layer. Provided information are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:84
msgid ""
"general such as name in the project, source path, list of auxiliary "
"files, last save time and size, the used provider"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:86
msgid ""
"custom properties, used to store in the active project additional "
"information about the layer. Default custom properties include "
":guilabel:`Identify/format`, which influences how the results from using "
"the |identify| :ref:`Identify features <raster_identify>` tool over a "
"raster layer are formatted. More properties can be created and managed "
"using PyQGIS, specifically through the :pyqgis:`setCustomProperty() "
"<qgis.core.QgsMapLayer.setCustomProperty>` method."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:1415
msgid "identify"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:91
msgid ""
"based on the provider of the layer: extent, width and height, data type, "
"GDAL driver, bands statistics"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:93
msgid ""
"the Coordinate Reference System: name, units, method, accuracy, reference"
" (i.e. whether it's static or dynamic)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:95
msgid ""
"read from layer properties: data type, extent, width/height, compression,"
" pixel size, statistics on bands, number of columns, rows and no-data "
"values of the raster..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:98
msgid ""
"picked from the :ref:`filled metadata <raster_metadata>`: access, "
"extents, links, contacts, history..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:104
msgid "Source Properties"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:106
msgid ""
"The |system| :guilabel:`Source` tab displays basic information about the "
"selected raster, including:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:109
msgid "the :guilabel:`Layer name` to display in the :guilabel:`Layers Panel`;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:110
msgid ""
"the :guilabel:`Coordinate Reference System`: Displays the layer's "
":ref:`Coordinate Reference System (CRS) <layer_crs>`. You can change the "
"layer's CRS, by selecting a recently used one in the drop-down list or "
"clicking on the |setProjection| :sup:`Select CRS` button (see "
":ref:`crs_selector`). Use this process only if the layer CRS is a wrong "
"or not specified. If you wish to reproject your data, use a reprojection "
"algorithm from Processing or :ref:`Save it as new dataset "
"<general_saveas>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:1465
msgid "setProjection"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:120
msgid ""
"Depending on the data provider, a :guilabel:`Layer source` group "
"indicates the path to the source of the dataset and allows for replacing "
"the loaded layer:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:123
msgid ""
"When the layer is stored as file on disk, edit the path shown in the text"
" box or press :guilabel:`...` :sup:`Browse` to select another file on the"
" disk"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:125
msgid ""
"When the layer is provided by an ArcGIS MapServer service, it is possible"
" to modify its :ref:`authentication settings <authentication>`, while "
"keeping unchanged the details for connecting to the service."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:128
msgid ""
"For an XYZ remote layer, it is possible to modify at the layer level any "
"of its :ref:`connection details <xyz_tile>` (URL, authentication "
"settings, zoom levels, resolution, ...). Modifications are applied to the"
" layer without altering the original connection settings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:140
msgid "Raster Layer Properties - Source Dialog"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:149
msgid "Symbology Properties"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:151
msgid "The raster layer symbology tab is made of three different sections:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:153
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Band rendering` where you can control the renderer type to"
" use"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:154
msgid "The :guilabel:`Layer rendering` to apply effects on rendered data"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:155
msgid "The :guilabel:`Resampling` methods to optimize rendering on map"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:158
msgid "Band rendering"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:160
msgid ""
"QGIS offers many different :guilabel:`Render types`. The choice of "
"renderer depends on the data type and the information you'd like to "
"highlight."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:164
msgid ""
":ref:`Multiband color <multiband_color>` - if the file comes with several"
" bands (e.g. a satellite image with several bands)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:166
msgid ""
":ref:`Paletted/Unique values <paletted>` - for single band files that "
"come with an indexed palette (e.g. a digital topographic map) or for "
"general use of palettes for rendering raster layers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:169
msgid ""
":ref:`Singleband gray <singleband_gray>` - (one band of) the image will "
"be rendered as gray. QGIS will choose this renderer if the file is "
"neither multiband nor paletted (e.g. a shaded relief map)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:173
msgid ""
":ref:`Singleband pseudocolor <label_colormaptab>` - this renderer can be "
"used for files with a continuous palette or color map (e.g. an elevation "
"map)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:176
msgid ""
":ref:`Single color <singlecolor>` - the raster layer will be rendered "
"with a single color."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:178
msgid ":ref:`Hillshade <hillshade_renderer>` - Creates hillshade from a band."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:180
msgid ""
":ref:`Contours <raster_contours>` - Generates contours on the fly for a "
"source raster band."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:187
msgid "Multiband color"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:189
msgid ""
"With the multiband color renderer, three selected bands from the image "
"will be used as the red, green or blue component of the color image. QGIS"
" automatically fetches :guilabel:`Min` and :guilabel:`Max` values for "
"each band of the raster and scales the coloring accordingly. You can "
"control the value ranges in the :ref:`Min/Max Value Settings "
"<minmaxvalues>` section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:196
#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:276
msgid ""
"A :guilabel:`Contrast enhancement` method can be applied to the values: "
"'No enhancement', 'Stretch to MinMax', 'Stretch and clip to MinMax' and "
"'Clip to min max'."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:202
msgid "**Contrast enhancement**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:204
msgid ""
"When adding GRASS rasters, the option *Contrast enhancement* will always "
"be set automatically to *stretch to min max*, even if this is set to "
"another value in the QGIS general options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:213
msgid "Raster Symbology - Multiband color rendering"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:216
msgid "**Viewing a Single Band of a Multiband Raster**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:218
msgid ""
"If you want to view a single band of a multiband image (for example, "
"Red), you might think you would set the Green and Blue bands to "
":guilabel:`Not Set`. But the preferred way of doing this is to set the "
"image type to :ref:`Singleband gray <singleband_gray>`, and then select "
"Red as the :guilabel:`Gray band` to use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:229
msgid "Paletted/Unique values"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:231
msgid ""
"This is the standard render option for singleband files that include a "
"color table, where a certain color is assigned to each pixel value. In "
"that case, the palette is rendered automatically."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:235
msgid ""
"It can be used for all kinds of raster bands, assigning a color to each "
"unique raster value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:238
msgid ""
"If you want to change a color, just double-click on the color and the "
":guilabel:`Select color` dialog appears."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:241
msgid ""
"It is also possible to assign labels to the colors. The label will then "
"appear in the legend of the raster layer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:244
msgid ""
"Right-clicking over selected rows in the color table shows a contextual "
"menu to:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:247
msgid ":guilabel:`Change Color...` for the selection"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:248
msgid ":guilabel:`Change Opacity...` for the selection"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:249
msgid ":guilabel:`Change Label...` for the selection"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:256
msgid "Raster Symbology - Paletted unique value rendering"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:258
msgid ""
"The pulldown menu, that opens when clicking the :guilabel:`...` "
"(:sup:`Advanced options`) button below the color map to the right, offers"
" color map loading (:guilabel:`Load Color Map from File...`) and "
"exporting (:guilabel:`Export Color Map to File...`), and loading of "
"classes (:guilabel:`Load Classes from Layer`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:268
msgid "Singleband gray"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:270
msgid ""
"This renderer allows you to render a layer using only one band with a "
":guilabel:`Color gradient`: 'Black to white' or 'White to black'. You can"
" change the range of values to color (:guilabel:`Min` and "
":guilabel:`Max`) in the :ref:`Min/Max Value Settings <minmaxvalues>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:285
msgid "Raster Symbology - Singleband gray rendering"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:287
msgid ""
"Pixels are assigned a color based on the selected color gradient and the "
"layer's legend (in the :guilabel:`Layers` panel and the layout "
":ref:`legend item <layout_legend_item>`) is displayed using a continuous "
"color ramp. Press :guilabel:`Legend settings...` if you wish to tweak the"
" settings. More details at :ref:`raster_legend_settings`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:298
msgid "Singleband pseudocolor"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:300
msgid ""
"This is a render option for single-band files that include a continuous "
"palette. You can also create color maps for a band of a multiband raster."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:309
msgid "Raster Symbology - Singleband pseudocolor rendering"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:312
msgid ""
"Using a :guilabel:`Band` of the layer and a :ref:`values range "
"<minmaxvalues>`, you can now interpolate and assign representation color "
"to pixels within classes. More at :ref:`color_ramp_shader`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:316
msgid ""
"Pixels are assigned a color based on the selected color ramp and the "
"layer's legend (in the :guilabel:`Layers` panel and the layout "
":ref:`legend item <layout_legend_item>`) is displayed using a continuous "
"color ramp. Press :guilabel:`Legend settings...` if you wish to tweak the"
" settings or instead use a legend with separated classes (and colors). "
"More details at :ref:`raster_legend_settings`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:326
msgid "Single color"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:328
msgid ""
"This renderer allows you to render a raster layer using :guilabel:`Single"
" color`. This type of renderer is useful when you want to display a "
"raster layer uniformly, without any variation in color based on pixel "
"values."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:332
msgid ""
"The single color renderer can be used with both single-band and multiband"
" raster layers. When used with multiband rasters, you can select which "
"band to apply the single color to, effectively displaying that specific "
"band uniformly across the entire layer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:341
msgid "Raster Symbology - Single color rendering"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:347
msgid "Hillshade"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:349
msgid "Render a band of the raster layer using hillshading."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:356
msgid "Raster Symbology - Hillshade rendering"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:358
#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:386
msgid "Options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:360
msgid ":guilabel:`Band`: The raster band to use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:361
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Altitude`: The elevation angle of the light source (default is"
" ``45°``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:363
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Azimuth`: The azimuth of the light source (default is "
"``315°``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:365
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Z Factor`: Scaling factor for the values of the raster band "
"(default is ``1``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:367
msgid ""
"|checkbox| :guilabel:`Multidirectional`: Specify if multidirectional "
"hillshading is to be used (default is ``off``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:1391
msgid "checkbox"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:373
msgid "Contours"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:375
msgid ""
"This renderer draws contour lines that are calculated on the fly from the"
" source raster band."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:384
msgid "Raster Symbology - Contours rendering"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:388
msgid ":guilabel:`Input band`: the raster band to use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:389
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Contour interval`: the distance between two consecutive "
"contour lines"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:390
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Contour symbol`: the :ref:`symbol <vector_line_symbols>` to "
"apply to the common contour lines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:392
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Index contour interval`: the distance between two consecutive "
"**index contours**, that is the lines shown in a distinctive manner for "
"ease of identification, being commonly printed more heavily than other "
"contour lines and generally labeled with a value along its course."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:396
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Index contour symbol`: the symbol to apply to the index "
"contour lines"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:397
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Input downscaling`: Indicates by how much the renderer will "
"scale down the request to the data provider (default is ``4.0``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:400
msgid ""
"For example, if you generate contour lines on input raster block with the"
" same size as the output raster block, the generated lines would contain "
"too much detail. This detail can be reduced by the \"downscale\" factor, "
"requesting lower resolution of the source raster. For a raster block "
"1000x500 with downscale 10, the renderer will request raster 100x50 from "
"provider. Higher downscale makes contour lines more simplified (at the "
"expense of losing some detail)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:411
msgid "Setting the min and max values"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:413
msgid ""
"By default, QGIS reports the :guilabel:`Min` and :guilabel:`Max` values "
"of the band(s) of the raster. A few very low and/or high values can have "
"a negative impact on the rendering of the raster. The :guilabel:`Min/Max "
"Value Settings` frame helps you control the rendering."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:425
msgid "Raster Symbology - Min and Max Value Settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:428
msgid "Available options are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:430
msgid ""
"|radioButtonOff| :guilabel:`User defined`: The default :guilabel:`Min` "
"and :guilabel:`Max` values of the band(s) can be overridden"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:1451
msgid "radioButtonOff"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:433
msgid ""
"|radioButtonOff| :guilabel:`Cumulative count cut`: Removes outliers. The "
"standard range of values is ``2%`` to ``98%``, but it can be adapted "
"manually."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:436
msgid ""
"|radioButtonOn| :guilabel:`Min / max`: Uses the whole range of values in "
"the image band."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:1453
msgid "radioButtonOn"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:438
msgid ""
"|radioButtonOff| :guilabel:`Mean +/- standard deviation x`: Creates a "
"color table that only considers values within the standard deviation or "
"within multiple standard deviations. This is useful when you have one or "
"two cells with abnormally high values in a raster layer that impact the "
"rendering of the raster negatively."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:445
msgid "Calculations of the min and max values of the bands are made based on the:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:448
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Statistics extent`: it can be :guilabel:`Whole raster`, "
":guilabel:`Current canvas` or :guilabel:`Updated canvas`. "
":guilabel:`Updated canvas` means that min/max values used for the "
"rendering will change with the canvas extent (dynamic stretching)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:452
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Accuracy`, which can be either :guilabel:`Estimate (faster)` "
"or :guilabel:`Actual (slower)`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:455
msgid ""
"For some settings, you may need to press the :guilabel:`Apply` button of "
"the layer properties dialog in order to display the actual min and max "
"values in the widgets."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:462
msgid "Color ramp shader classification"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:464
msgid ""
"This method can be used to classify and represent scalar dataset (raster "
"or mesh contour) based on their values. Given a :ref:`color ramp <color-"
"ramp>` and a number of classes, it generates intermediate color map "
"entries for class limits. Each color is mapped with a value interpolated "
"from a range of values and according to a classification mode. The scalar"
" dataset elements are then assigned their color based on their class."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:476
msgid "Classifying a dataset with a color ramp shader"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:478
msgid ""
"A :guilabel:`Min` and :guilabel:`Max` values must be defined and used to "
"interpolate classes bounds. By default QGIS detects them from the dataset"
" but they can be modified."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:481
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Interpolation` entry defines how scalar elements are "
"assigned their color :"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:484
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Discrete` (a ``<=`` symbol appears in the header of the "
":guilabel:`Value` column): The color is taken from the closest color map "
"entry with equal or higher value"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:487
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Linear`: The color is linearly interpolated from the color map"
" entries above and below the pixel value, meaning that to each dataset "
"value corresponds a unique color"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:490
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Exact` (a ``=`` symbol appears in the header of the "
":guilabel:`Value` column): Only pixels with value equal to a color map "
"entry are applied a color; others are not rendered."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:493
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Color ramp` widget helps you select the color ramp to "
"assign to the dataset. As usual with :ref:`this widget "
"<color_ramp_widget>`, you can create a new one and edit or save the "
"currently selected one. The name of the color ramp will be saved in the "
"configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:497
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Label unit suffix` adds a label after the value in the "
"legend, and the :guilabel:`Label precision` controls the number of "
"decimals to display."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:500
msgid ""
"The classification :guilabel:`Mode` helps you define how values are "
"distributed across the classes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:503
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Equal interval`: Provided the :guilabel:`Number of classes`, "
"limits values are defined so that the classes all have the same "
"magnitude."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:505
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Continuous`: Classes number and color are fetched from the "
"color ramp stops; limits values are set following stops distribution in "
"the color ramp."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:508
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Quantile`: Provided the :guilabel:`Number of classes`, limits "
"values are defined so that the classes have the same number of elements. "
"Not available with :ref:`mesh layers <mesh_symbology_contours>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:511
msgid "You can then :guilabel:`Classify` or tweak the classes:"
msgstr ""

