#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:1195
msgid ""
"A Raster Attribute Table links raster values (or value ranges) to "
"descriptive attributes such as class names, pixel counts, and colors. "
"RATs are commonly used for classified rasters, color tables, and "
"histogram information, helping QGIS interpret how raster values should be"
" displayed and classified."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_raster/raster_properties.rst:1201
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Attribute Tables` tab allows you to view and edit raster "
"attribute data. To access the attribute table of a raster layer, right-"
"click the layer in the layers panel, open :guilabel:`Properties...` and "
"select :guilabel:`Attribute Tables`."
